# StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new + this file together close the MITM
# window at first connect AND key rotation. The first operator to clone
# the repo populates this file (ssh-keyscan auto-fills on first contact);
# subsequent operators consume the committed keys without prompting; key
# rotation requires an explicit PR replacing the line(s) below.
#
# Bootstrap (initial seed already populated by Phase 45 plan executor):
#   ssh-keyscan -H 192.168.1.50 >> scripts/.ssh-known-hosts
#   git add scripts/.ssh-known-hosts && git commit
#
# Rotation:
#   1. Operator pre-commits new host line(s) (ssh-keyscan -H 192.168.1.50)
#   2. PR review verifies fingerprint match against an out-of-band channel
#      (e.g. console-of-record at the Proxmox host).
#   3. Merge → all runners + CI pick up the new key.
#
